cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ApprenticeOps (benchmark, harness, or data), please cite it as below."
title: "ApprenticeOps: Evaluating Small Locally-Sovereign LLMs as Homelab Operations Assistants"
abstract: >-
  An open, reproducible benchmark and CPU-telemetry method for evaluating small
  (0.5-8B), quantized, fully-offline local LLMs as homelab/edge operations
  assistants. It profiles judged quality, destructive-action safety, and energy
  together on commodity offline hardware over frozen real GitOps incidents, and
  reduces model selection to a measured quality x safety x energy Pareto front on
  which the usual proxies (parameter count, benchmark score, a "reasoning" badge,
  perplexity) select dominated models.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hont
    given-names: Dragos
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/dragoshont/apprenticeops"
url: "https://github.com/dragoshont/apprenticeops"
